<div id="myDIV" class="header">
    <h2 style="margin:5px">My Algorithm</h2>
    <input type="text" id="myInput" placeholder="Please enter the next step in your algorithm">
    <span onclick="newElement()" class="addBtn">Add</span>
</div>

<ul id="myUL">
    <div contenteditable="true"><li>Here is where you write all the steps in your algorithm!</li>
        {{#pname}}
            <li class="closeable">Your function's name is: {{newname}} <br>
                Your function takes this parameter: {{newParameterType}} {{newParameterName}} <br>
                You plan on returning: {{newReturnType}} {{newReturnName}} <br>
                Your Description: {{description}}
            </li>
        {{/pname}}
        <li class="closeable">Try to be specific and think "line by line" how your code should work</li>
        <li class="closeable">You can add, delete, and edit steps</li>
        <li class="checked closeable">Not sure you want to delete a step? Just cross it out by tapping the line!</li>
        <li class="closeable">Stuck? Maybe consider creating a variable so you can access your input</li>
        <li class="closeable">Stuck? Consider using a data structure</li>
        <li class="closeable">Stuck? Need to repeat a step? Consider creating a for-loop</li>
        <li class="closeable">Stuck? Did you remember to return your result?</li>
    </div>
</ul>

<script src="../js/mainPage.js"></script>

<form>
    <button type="submit" id="save" class="button" formaction="saves">Save</button>
    <button type="submit" class="button" formaction="login">Save and Quit</button>
    <button type="submit" class="button" formaction="suggestions">See My Code Recommendations</button>
</form>

